  stimulus_text = 'When visiting a national park, it is essential to be prepared for a variety of weather conditions. Pack layers of clothing, rain gear, and sunscreen, regardless of the season. If you plan to hike, bring plenty of water and snacks. If you are going to camp, make sure you have a permit and familiarize yourself with the park’s rules and regulations.  Be sure to dispose of trash properly, leaving no trace of your presence.  What should you do if you see an animal in the park?',
